  4 This and the three following verses wear the appearance of having been inserted at a later period to meet objections respecting the number of the angels who guard hell, raised by the Jews; perhaps at Medina, as the four classes of persons specified are those whom Muhammad had to deal with in that city, viz
, the Jews, Believers, the Hypocrites, or undecided, and Idolaters
 These are constantly mentioned together in the Medina Suras
