-THE OPENING [V
]  MECCA
-8 Verses  In the Name of God, the Compassionate, the Merciful  HAVE we not OPENED thine heart for thee?  And taken off from thee thy burden,  Which galled thy back?  And have we not raised thy name for thee?  Then verily along with trouble cometh ease
  Verily along with trouble cometh ease
  But when thou art set at liberty, then prosecute thy toil
  And seek thy Lord with fervour
