  To you be your religion; to me my religion
1   _______________________  1 This Sura is said to have been revealed when Walîd urged Muhammad to consent that his God should be worshipped at the same time with the old Meccan deities, or alternately every year
 Hishâmi, p
 79; Tabari, p
 139
 It is a distinct renunciation of Meccan idolatry, as the following Sura is a distinct recognition of the Divine Unity
