  16 This passage has been supposed to refer to Salman the Persian
 He did not, however, embrace Islam till a much later period, at Medina
 Nöld
 p
 110
 Mr
 Muir thinks that it may refer to Suheib, son of Sinan, "the first fruits of Greece," as Muhammad styled him, who, while yet a boy, had been carried off by some Greeks as a slave, from Mesopotamia to Syria, brought by a party of the Beni Kalb, and sold to Abdallah ibn Jodda'ân of Mecca
 He became rich, and embraced Islam
