  35 It appears to have been the custom of the idolatrous Arabs to set apart one portion of their fields for the Supreme God, and the other for the inferior gods represented by their idols
 If any of the fruit happened to fall from the part consecrated to the idols into that consecrated to God, they restored it, but if the reverse occurred, they gave it to the idols
 God, said they, is rich and can dispense with it
 The secret, however, was that the idols' portion was reserved for the priests, Beidhawi
