  45 That is, does not weigh the evidence for Muhammad's mission already given, but demands, as the Jews did, to see God himself
  46 In all Muhammadan countries the first time of prayer is the moghreb or sunset, or rather, four minutes later; the second the eshe, when it has become quite dark; the third the soobh or fegr, the daybreak; the fourth, doohr, or a little after noon, when the sun has begun to decline; the fifth, the asr, midway between noon and nightfall
 The obligatory legal alms or impost are called, as here, zekah (lit
 purity), the voluntary, sudackah
 It is, however, left to the conscience of individuals to give and to apply them as they think fit
