  79 The greater Pilgrimage, which every Muslim is bound to perform once in his life, is the Hadjat el Farz (the one obligatory Pilgrimage), or the Hadjat el Islam
 The Umrah, or little pilgrimage, may be performed at any time except the pilgrimage season, and its ceremonies are much fewer
 They are described by Lieut
